The trail includes an unofficial, unimproved section to the north of Wallkill, and is bounded by NY 52 and NY 208. The land was purchased by the towns of Montgomery and Shawangunk in 1985 and converted to a public trail. The total cost of paving the trail was expected to be $750,000, though it eventually ballooned to $1.5 million.
